#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.40:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga "
msgstr "4. Messengers from the Gods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Ādhipateyyasutta "
msgstr "40. In Charge "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.148, sc1
msgctxt "an3.40:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, ādhipateyyāni. "
msgstr "“There are, mendicants, these three things to put in charge. "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.3"
msgid "Attādhipateyyaṃ, lokādhipateyyaṃ, dhammādhipateyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Putting oneself, the world, or the teaching in charge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.40:1.4"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, attādhipateyyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is putting oneself in charge? "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, and reflects like this: "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.6"
msgid "‘na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "‘I didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness for the sake of a robe, "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.7"
msgid "Na piṇḍapātahetu, na senāsanahetu, na itibhavābhavahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "alms-food, lodgings, or rebirth in this or that state. "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.8"
msgid "Api ca khomhi otiṇṇo jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto. "
msgstr "But I was swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I was swamped by suffering, mired in suffering. "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.9"
msgid "Appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethāti. "
msgstr "And I thought, “Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.” "

#. VAR: yādisake → yādisake vā (bj, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: vā → ca (mr)
#. VAR: vā → ca (mr)
msgctxt "an3.40:1.10"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana yādisake kāme ohāya agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito tādisake vā kāme pariyeseyyaṃ tato vā pāpiṭṭhatare, na metaṃ patirūpan’ti. "
msgstr "But it would not be appropriate for me to seek sensual pleasures like those I abandoned when I went forth, or even worse.’ "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.11"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.12"
msgid "‘āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ bhavissati asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggan’ti. "
msgstr "‘My energy shall be roused up and unflagging, mindfulness shall be established and lucid, my body shall be tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind shall be immersed in samādhi.’ "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.13"
msgid "So attānaṃyeva adhipatiṃ karitvā akusalaṃ pajahati, kusalaṃ bhāveti, sāvajjaṃ pajahati, anavajjaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "Putting themselves in charge, they give up the unskillful and develop the skillful, they give up the blameworthy and develop the blameless, and they keep themselves pure. "

msgctxt "an3.40:1.14"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, attādhipateyyaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called putting oneself in charge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.149, sc2
msgctxt "an3.40:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, lokādhipateyyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is putting the world in charge? "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, and reflects like this: "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.3"
msgid "‘na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "‘I didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness for the sake of a robe, "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.4"
msgid "Na piṇḍapātahetu, na senāsanahetu, na itibhavābhavahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "alms-food, lodgings, or rebirth in this or that state. "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.5"
msgid "Api ca khomhi otiṇṇo jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto. "
msgstr "But I was swamped by rebirth, old age, and death, by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I was swamped by suffering, mired in suffering. "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.6"
msgid "Appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti. "
msgstr "And I thought, “Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.” "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.7"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana evaṃ pabbajito samāno kāmavitakkaṃ vā vitakkeyyaṃ, byāpādavitakkaṃ vā vitakkeyyaṃ, vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ vā vitakkeyyaṃ, mahā kho panāyaṃ lokasannivāso. "
msgstr "And now, since I’ve now gone forth, I might have sensual, malicious, or cruel thoughts. But the population of the world is large, "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.8"
msgid "Mahantasmiṃ kho pana lokasannivāse santi samaṇabrāhmaṇā iddhimanto dibbacakkhukā paracittaviduno. "
msgstr "and there are ascetics and brahmins who have psychic power—they’re clairvoyant, and can read the minds of others. "

#. VAR: pajānanti → jānanti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.40:2.9"
msgid "Te dūratopi passanti, āsannāpi na dissanti, cetasāpi cittaṃ pajānanti. "
msgstr "They see far without being seen, even by those close; and they understand the minds of others. "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.10"
msgid "Tepi maṃ evaṃ jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "They would know me: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.40:2.11"
msgid "‘passatha, bho, imaṃ kulaputtaṃ saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito samāno vokiṇṇo viharati pāpakehi akusalehi dhammehī’ti. "
msgstr "“Look at this gentleman; they’ve gone forth out of faith from the lay life to homelessness, but they’re living mixed up with bad, unskillful qualities.” "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.12"
msgid "devatāpi kho santi iddhimantiniyo dibbacakkhukā paracittaviduniyo. "
msgstr "And there are deities, too, who have psychic power—they’re clairvoyant, and can read the minds of others. "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.13"
msgid "Tā dūratopi passanti, āsannāpi na dissanti, cetasāpi cittaṃ jānanti. "
msgstr "They see far without being seen, even by those close; and they understand the minds of others. "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.14"
msgid "Tāpi maṃ evaṃ jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "They would know me: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.40:2.15"
msgid "‘passatha, bho, imaṃ kulaputtaṃ saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito samāno vokiṇṇo viharati pāpakehi akusalehi dhammehī’ti. "
msgstr "“Look at this gentleman; they’ve gone forth out of faith from the lay life to homelessness, but they’re living mixed up with bad, unskillful qualities.”’ "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.16"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.17"
msgid "‘āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ bhavissati asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggan’ti. "
msgstr "‘My energy shall be roused up and unflagging, mindfulness shall be established and lucid, my body shall be tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind shall be immersed in samādhi.’ "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.18"
msgid "So lokaṃyeva adhipatiṃ karitvā akusalaṃ pajahati, kusalaṃ bhāveti, sāvajjaṃ pajahati, anavajjaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "Putting the world in charge, they give up the unskillful and develop the skillful, they give up the blameworthy and develop the blameless, and they keep themselves pure. "

msgctxt "an3.40:2.19"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, lokādhipateyyaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called putting the world in charge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.40:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammādhipateyyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what, mendicants, is putting the teaching in charge? "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, and reflects like this: "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.3"
msgid "‘na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "‘I didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness for the sake of a robe, "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.4"
msgid "Na piṇḍapātahetu, na senāsanahetu, na itibhavābhavahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "alms-food, lodgings, or rebirth in this or that state. "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.5"
msgid "Api ca khomhi otiṇṇo jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto. "
msgstr "But I was swamped by rebirth, old age, and death, by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I was swamped by suffering, mired in suffering. "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.6"
msgid "Appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethāti. "
msgstr "And I thought, “Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.” "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.7"
msgid "Svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhīti. "
msgstr "The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.8"
msgid "Santi kho pana me sabrahmacārī jānaṃ passaṃ viharanti. "
msgstr "I have spiritual companions who live knowing and seeing. "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.9"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajito samāno kusīto vihareyyaṃ pamatto, na metaṃ assa patirūpan’ti. "
msgstr "Now that I’ve gone forth in this well explained teaching and training, it would not be appropriate for me to live lazy and heedless.’ "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.10"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.11"
msgid "‘āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ bhavissati asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggan’ti. "
msgstr "‘My energy shall be roused up and unflagging, mindfulness shall be established and lucid, my body shall be tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind shall be immersed in samādhi.’ "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.12"
msgid "So dhammaṃyeva adhipatiṃ karitvā akusalaṃ pajahati, kusalaṃ bhāveti, sāvajjaṃ pajahati, anavajjaṃ bhāveti, suddhaṃ attānaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "Putting the teaching in charge, they give up the unskillful and develop the skillful, they give up the blameworthy and develop the blameless, and they keep themselves pure. "

msgctxt "an3.40:3.13"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammādhipateyyaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called putting the teaching in charge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.40:3.14"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi ādhipateyyānīti. "
msgstr "These are the three things to put in charge. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.40:4.1"
msgid "Natthi loke raho nāma, "
msgstr "There’s no privacy in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.2"
msgid "pāpakammaṃ pakubbato; "
msgstr "for someone who does bad deeds. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.3"
msgid "Attā te purisa jānāti, "
msgstr "You’ll know for yourself, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:4.4"
msgid "saccaṃ vā yadi vā musā. "
msgstr "whether you’ve lied or told the truth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.40:5.1"
msgid "Kalyāṇaṃ vata bho sakkhi, "
msgstr "When you witness your good self, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.2"
msgid "attānaṃ atimaññasi; "
msgstr "you despise it; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.3"
msgid "Yo santaṃ attani pāpaṃ, "
msgstr "while you disguise "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:5.4"
msgid "attānaṃ parigūhasi. "
msgstr "your bad self inside yourself. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.150, sc6
msgctxt "an3.40:6.1"
msgid "Passanti devā ca tathāgatā ca, "
msgstr "The gods and the Realized One see "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.2"
msgid "Lokasmiṃ bālaṃ visamaṃ carantaṃ; "
msgstr "the fool who lives unjustly in the world. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: attādhipateyyako ca → attādhipako sato care (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.40:6.3"
msgid "Tasmā hi attādhipateyyako ca, "
msgstr "So with yourself in charge, live mindfully; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.4"
msgid "Lokādhipo ca nipako ca jhāyī; "
msgstr "with the world in charge, be alert and practice absorption; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.5"
msgid "Dhammādhipo ca anudhammacārī, "
msgstr "with the teaching in charge, live in line with that teaching: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:6.6"
msgid "Na hīyati saccaparakkamo muni. "
msgstr "a sage who tries for the truth doesn’t deteriorate. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.40:7.1"
msgid "Pasayha māraṃ abhibhuyya antakaṃ, "
msgstr "Māra’s destroyed; the terminator’s overcome: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.2"
msgid "Yo ca phusī jātikkhayaṃ padhānavā; "
msgstr "one who strives reaches the end of rebirth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.3"
msgid "So tādiso lokavidū sumedho, "
msgstr "Poised, clever, knowing the world—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:7.4"
msgid "Sabbesu dhammesu atammayo munī”ti. "
msgstr "that sage identifies with nothing at all.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.40:7.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.40:7.6"
msgid "Devadūtavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.40:8.1"
msgid "Brahma ānanda sāriputto, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.2"
msgid "Nidānaṃ hatthakena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.3"
msgid "Dūtā duve ca rājāno, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.40:8.4"
msgid "Sukhumālādhipateyyena cāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
